Welcome to the bubble shooter!
When you first enter into the game you will be presented with a pink 
"opening screen" where you will have to enter p to surpass this and begin playing

While playing you have 3 main controllers. the left and right arrow to move
your shooter and the space bar to shoot the bullet from the angle you choose.
Other options included in the game 
Q to quit
R to reset (available after the game is over only!)

object of the game is to pop all the bubbles before they get to the bottom
without hitting the black!

Black is the "death bubble" and when hit will immediately wash out the game 
ultimately bringing up the end screen and giving you the option to restart from 
level one or quit altogether.

Happy playing Bubble Shooter!




***DISCLAIMERS***
for testing reasons the game is set to be shorter (30 points to level up and 
more black bubbles) This presents the opportunity to test all factors while also 
not taking a million years! happy to set it to how it is meant to be played 
but figured you might appreciate this for purpose of grading

I struggled in a few different areas but really felt this program helped me grow! 
For collision detection, I think my biggest issue is the math being off- reread 
and reworked my logic many times but when the math of the game doesn't recognize
the proper positioning it can't always tell when the bubbles match leaving some
random bubbles that I tried endlessly to resolve. That being said this code is 
closest I could get to it with the way I set it up. 
This may be a more basic program than some other classmates but I am very happy
with the progress I made and do feel this helped me grow a lot as did our class! 